<subSubSection id="16A05544DA4416062F927E7B75A98393" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="253305CB026E2721276A1803A61A009E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C50C6E446ADFFAEFBFFAF36EAFCA5BA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
(based on 
<bibRefCitation id="099A56D5AF77E6C55606D9E99E2AB5F8" author="Ohira, H" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B8" refString="Ohira, H, 1972. Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera). Pacific Insects 14: 1 - 14" title="Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera)." volume="14" year="1972">
<normalizedToken id="F58DD14901DD9F5CFFEB828FC6F2A576" originalValue="Ôhira">Ohira</normalizedToken>
1972
</bibRefCitation>
and the figures of holotype and one paratype provided by BPBM). Body length 4.0 mm, width 1.7 mm (based on holotype; see 
<bibRefCitation id="8240489847E55960C8A44BC727B734FC" author="Ohira, H" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B8" refString="Ohira, H, 1972. Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera). Pacific Insects 14: 1 - 14" title="Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera)." volume="14" year="1972">
<normalizedToken id="BD4BB7B021257FB961A30E9F1CACDD0C" originalValue="Ôhira">Ohira</normalizedToken>
1972
</bibRefCitation>
). Body reddish brown (examined paratype darker than holotype; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EC1BF6BD8A9CB90F2F8F6BA0056444A9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus and characters of Pseudocsikia formosana (Ohira, 1972) A-H male holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C habitus, lateral view D labels E anterior protrusion of pronotum (indicated by an arrow), dorsal view F anterior protrusion of hypomeron (indicated by an arrow), ventral view G posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view H abdominal tip, ventral view (arrow indicates the apex of median lobe) I, J paratype of an unknown sex I habitus, dorsal view J labels. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A-C, I); E-H not to scale. All photos provided by Jeremy Frank (BPBM)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691081" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">2A-C, I</figureCitation>
), outer margins of pronotum and elytra, underside, and legs paler. Antenna exceeding posterior angle of pronotum by about apical two antennomeres (
<bibRefCitation id="00AFD4F8DCA44BA0ACF75A33B3FBF772" author="Ohira, H" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B8" refString="Ohira, H, 1972. Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera). Pacific Insects 14: 1 - 14" title="Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera)." volume="14" year="1972">
<normalizedToken id="B193E494C0A73834DA578E6475EEE958" originalValue="Ôhira">Ohira</normalizedToken>
1972
</bibRefCitation>
). Antennomere II slightly shorter than antennomere III (
<bibRefCitation id="930788411D588B42E9F54D2F55239881" author="Ohira, H" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B8" refString="Ohira, H, 1972. Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera). Pacific Insects 14: 1 - 14" title="Elaterid-beetles from Taiwan in Bishop Museum (Coleoptera)." volume="14" year="1972">
<normalizedToken id="60BCA56D20DA5B5A544A6E5A2BD1419A" originalValue="Ôhira">Ohira</normalizedToken>
1972
</bibRefCitation>
). Punctures on pronotum of moderate size, intervals between punctures mostly equal 3-5 puncture diameters, anterior protrusion of pronotum with apex laterad of center (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="21F0CB107457B1F1D5F01B1AB0FD101F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus and characters of Pseudocsikia formosana (Ohira, 1972) A-H male holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C habitus, lateral view D labels E anterior protrusion of pronotum (indicated by an arrow), dorsal view F anterior protrusion of hypomeron (indicated by an arrow), ventral view G posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view H abdominal tip, ventral view (arrow indicates the apex of median lobe) I, J paratype of an unknown sex I habitus, dorsal view J labels. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A-C, I); E-H not to scale. All photos provided by Jeremy Frank (BPBM)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691081" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">2E, F</figureCitation>
). Posterior angle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6353927F672E332A32982F01CC714C0C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus and characters of Pseudocsikia formosana (Ohira, 1972) A-H male holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C habitus, lateral view D labels E anterior protrusion of pronotum (indicated by an arrow), dorsal view F anterior protrusion of hypomeron (indicated by an arrow), ventral view G posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view H abdominal tip, ventral view (arrow indicates the apex of median lobe) I, J paratype of an unknown sex I habitus, dorsal view J labels. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A-C, I); E-H not to scale. All photos provided by Jeremy Frank (BPBM)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691081" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">2G</figureCitation>
) of pronotum long, straight and robust, apex blunt, inner margin with obtuse protrusion subapically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11E3BE15838A51DC4F49D6B823AB77FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Aedeagus with robust median lobe, twice as long as paramere; with large acute lateral processes near midlength, apex rectangular, with large subapical spines laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="73A16022F9FEFEE917F8A6B95B5774A8" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus and characters of Pseudocsikia formosana (Ohira, 1972) A-H male holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C habitus, lateral view D labels E anterior protrusion of pronotum (indicated by an arrow), dorsal view F anterior protrusion of hypomeron (indicated by an arrow), ventral view G posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view H abdominal tip, ventral view (arrow indicates the apex of median lobe) I, J paratype of an unknown sex I habitus, dorsal view J labels. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A-C, I); E-H not to scale. All photos provided by Jeremy Frank (BPBM)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691081" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">2H</figureCitation>
) (needle-like ventral sclerite not mentioned in 
